BOOKINGS ONLY.  
During level 2 we are based indoors at the Waiwhetu Fitness Centre located on Te Whiti Park. Limited free parking is available outside our centre and on Riverside Drive, with vehicle access via Whites Line East.  Parking is limited however overflow parking is available within Te Whiti Park.

You will need to wait and be observed for 15 minutes after your vaccination.
You must wear a facemask and keep your social distancing of 2meters inside our centre.

DO NOT ATTEND and PLEASE REBOOK If you are...

description:
NOTE: this venue is operating Tuesdays to Fridays under level 1 and 2. Vaccinations on Mondays will take place at Unichem Upper Hutt Pharmacy, 723 Fergusson Drive. Please keep an eye on our facebook page for updates and enter your cell number when booking (so we can contact you - the venue may change with alert levels). 
 
https://www.facebook.com/profile.php?id=100054237188521 
 
You will need to wait and be observed for 15 minutes after your vaccination.
  
You must wear a facemask and be prepared to expose your full shoulder and upper arm without removing the facemask.
 
Please park in the rear carpark and ensure you are dressed warmly enough for the weather as there may be a cue outside.  
  
DO NOT ATTEND – PLEASE REBOOK If you are unwell with cold or flu like symptoms, sore throat, cough a high fever etc, have been to any locations of interest, are awaiting a COVID test or have been asked to stay home and self isolate.
